[04:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'difficult to generate for existing image models. And by the way, this reflection flow is a plugin for Flux1Dev, which is one of the best open- source image generators out there. And then really'

[04:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'quickly, here\'s the process on how it works. So your prompt is first fed through this scaling noise component to get Flux to generate multiple images based on your prompt. So it generates'

[04:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'all these images in parallel or basically simultaneously. And then the model would choose the best image based on your prompt. by generating multiple images and choosing the best one. Well, you already improve the chance of'

[05:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'getting a better and more accurate image. And then there are two components it can go through. The first one is called scaling reflection. So this takes the image and then iteratively refineses the image based on your text prompt. So'

[05:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'if an object is missing or if the shape or color or appearance of the object is wrong, then it would keep refining the image until it reaches a photo which actually aligns with your prompt. Now in'

[05:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'addition to refining the image, the model can also use another LLM to enhance your prompt to provide better guidance for the image generation. So in this scaling prompt component, your'

[05:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'prompt is compared with the image and if the image is rejected by the verifier, in other words, if the image does not align with the prompt, then this external LLM would refine the prompt further to give Flux more guidance on'

[05:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'how to generate the image correctly. And again, it does so iteratively until eventually it gets an image that aligns with your prompt. So in theory, this should give you a much better and more'

