[18:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'model that we\'ve seen with most of the other image and video generators out there including stable diffusion and flux and hunen and juan. This is a completely different architecture. In the simplest sense, auto reggressive'

[18:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'means the model predicts the next video chunk based on the previous ones instead of generating the whole video at once. And by the way, this is the architecture that OpenAI\'s legendary GPT40 image generator uses as well. It\'s also an'

[19:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'auto reggressive model. So it kind of generates the image from top to bottom instead of just generating the entire image at once. Now, we\'re not sure if this architecture is the best one to use for video generation or not, but there'

[19:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
